Oil fouls swans
A COOKING oil spill is thought to have injured 37 swans at the mouth of the
Tweed at Berwick earlier this month. The National Rivers Authority is
investigating, while the swans are being treated at a special centre on the
town's quay.
Dirty dozen
A COUNTRY vicar has modelled a series of nude sculptures of the disciples. The
Rev Toddy Hoare, 47, worked on the panels during a three months sabbatical at
his vicarage. ``Parishioners are beginning to spark a bit now they've seen
them,'' said Mr Hoare, who runs eight hillside parishes in Herriot country near
Thirsk, North Yorkshire.
