<HEADLINE>Two hit by car</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974667796</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A 16-year-old girl was yesterday in a Kidderminster General Hospital's
intensive care unit after she and a friend were struck by a car which mounted
the pavement. Police said the accident happened on the A4112 at Tenbury Wells
in Hereford and Worcester on Tuesday night, leaving Katie Perkins, from Tenbury
Wells, with serious injuries. A 15-year-old Spanish girl, who was walking with
her sustained minor injuries.
</TEXT>
