<TEXT>
Petrol slump
MOTORISTS are buying less petrol than at any time in the past five years.
Figures show petrol sales slumped from 31.1 billion litres in 1990 to 29.4
billion last year. Sales rose in most other countries.
Watery grave
AN old fisherman has been buried with his TV remote control, tea and biscuits,
and the latest edition of Angling Times. ``We gave him the TV remote control
and the newspaper in case he wanted to catch up on the latest angling news,''
said 80-year-old Walter Davison's daughter Jillian, after the Lancashire
funeral.
