<HEADLINE>Baa-baas fall</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974667851</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Leicester 51, Barbarians 25
LEICESTER exploded with six second-half tries to equal a couple of records with
a half-century win over the Barbarians in this tradi- tional post-Christmas
extravaganza.
With wings Rory Underwood and Steve Hackney each streaming in for a brace of
tries, Leicester reached 51 points to equal their highest score in the fixture
that goes back to the first decade of the century.
Two years ago they also achieved 51 and yesterday's win was their fourth in
succession over the scratch team, equalling their best sequence, which they
have managed twice before.
The Barbarians seemed to have done all the hard work by leading at half-time
and becoming familiar with each others' styles in the first 40 minutes.
But the combination from seven nations, which included 10 internationalists,
cracked after the break and Leicester banged in their half-dozen scores in a
30-minute spell before the invitation team collected two late, irrelevant
scores.
Details:
Leicester - R Underwood 2t, Hackney 2t, Back 1t, Kardonni 1t, Richards 1t;
Harris 5c, 2p.
Barbarians - Berek 1t, Proctor 1t, Straeuli 1t; King 2c, 2p.
</TEXT>
