q LEEDS moved up to eighth in the Premiership table with a 2-0 win at Bolton -
but the United players believe they should be even higher.
Skipper Gary McAllister said: ``You look at the quality of players we have got
at this club and eighth isn't good enough.'' Defender David Wetherall, who
headed the second Leeds goal in 63 minutes to kill off bottom-placed Wanderers,
added: ``We are a better team than that and now we've got to prove it.''
Tomas Brolin, the #4.5m signing from Parma, had opened the scoring five minutes
before the break.
