<DATE>951228</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Plea to missing father</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974667868</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A YOUNG mother has spoken of her family's most worrying Christmas ever after
her husband vanished during a night out with colleagues.
Leslie Armstrong, 36, a draughtsman, went out with workmates a week ago, and
has not been seen since he left a public house on Windmill Brae in Aberdeen at
6.30pm.
Police say they are baffled by the disappearance.
On Christmas Day Carol Armstrong, of Drumgelloch Street, Airdrie, told
eight-year-old Scott and Gillian, 10, that their father had had to stay on at
work.
She said: ``Now I am just praying Leslie will get in touch for Scott's birthday
on Thursday.''
</TEXT>
