<TEXT>
q THE British Horseracing Board yesterday moved to guarantee racecourse action
in Britain this Saturday by sanctioning an extra all-weather fixture at
Wolverhampton this weekend.
With snow and frost having already produced three successive blank days for the
sport and tomorrow's fixtures also under threat, race planners reacted by
ensuring at least some British racing during betting shop hours.
The Midlands track is already hosting an evening meeting on Saturday but will
now stage a ``double-header'' with a six-race card beginning at 12.55 and
ending at 3.25 before racing resumes under floodlights from 7.0 until 9.30.
</TEXT>
